<subSubSection id="C30F0386B13DFF98FF55FD1FFC72FB6C" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13DFF98FF55FD1FFE24FBEC" blockId="8.[166,1225,762,1236]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of face with facial carina; no ocellar setae; parafacial in profile twice as wide as flagellomere 1 (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FBCEFCFFFB31FC8C" box="[1088,1207,794,820]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionStartId-1="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" captionStartId-2="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox-0="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetBox-1="[263,1145,180,1601]" captionTargetBox-2="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId-0="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetId-1="figure-5@9.[191,1208,174,1626]" captionTargetId-2="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionTargetPageId-2="11" captionText-0="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." captionText-1="Fig. 4. Eupyrgota armipes, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — fore trochanter; 9 — mid trochanter; 10 — wing; 11 — mesonotum and abdomen, dorsally; 12 — abdomen, posterior." captionText-2="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
fig. 3, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FB02FCFFFB31FC8C" box="[1164,1207,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">3–5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), mesonotum and abdomen reddish yellow with a few brown or black spots or without them; scutellum with three pairs of long golden yellow setae; wing almost uniformly hyaline with yellow veins, without spots or bands (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FC9EFC9FFCC9FC2C" box="[784,847,890,916]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FCD3FC9FFCEDFC2C" box="[861,875,890,916]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FCD3FC9FFCEDFC2C" box="[861,875,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">6</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); fore coxa unmodified; fore and mid trochanters with spinulose brown setulae; fore femur without long setae, except 2 subbasal ventral setae, mid femur without femoral organ (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FC00FC5FFC49FC6C" box="[910,975,954,980]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13DFF98FC50FC5FFC6AFC6C" box="[990,1004,954,980]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[166,1231,602,1679]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Eupyrgota vespiformis, ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–4 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — left anterior; 4 — dorsal); 5 — wing; 6–7 — abdomen (6 — left; 7— dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FC50FC5FFC6AFC6C" box="[990,1004,954,980]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
); setae in ventroapical rows brown, spurious; abdominal sternites sparsely yellow setose; ventral hooks on oviscape strong; most setae brown to reddish yellow, setulae golden yellow. The presence of more than two scutellar setae and strong hooks on the oviscape supports its placement in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13DFF98FF48FBDEFEC6FBEC" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[198,320,1083,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FF48FBDEFEC6FBEC" box="[198,320,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. str.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13DFF98FF55FBBFFC72FB6C" blockId="8.[166,1225,762,1236]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">
R e m a r k s. This species possesses all the characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13DFF98FCDDFBBEFC4CFBCC" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[851,970,1115,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FCDDFBBEFC4CFBCC" box="[851,970,1115,1140]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. str.), and I transfer it to the nominal subgenus. However, it shows apparently no essential differences from 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13DFF98FF28FB7EFD8CFB0D" authority="(Hendel, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[166,522,1178,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavopilosa">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FF28FB7EFEC1FB0C" box="[166,327,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">E. flavopilosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB13DFF98FED2FB7FFD84FB0D" author="Hendel, F." box="[348,514,1178,1205]" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" pagination="77 - 117" refId="ref10493" refString="Hendel, F. Neue Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pyrgotinen // Archiv fur Naturgeschichte. - 1914 (1913). - 79 A, N 11. - S. 77 - 117 + 1 Taf." type="book chapter" year="1914">Hendel, 1914</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13DFF98FDDFFB7EFC03FB0C" authority="Chen, 1947" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[593,901,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosetosa">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13DFF98FDDFFB7EFD6CFB0C" box="[593,746,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="119">E. rufosetosa</emphasis>
Chen, 1947
</taxonomicName>
. Thorough comparison of existing material is needed to see if these nominal species are synonyms.
</paragraph>
